transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, hi, my name's Craig Dawson.

Speaker 1: I called last month and asked that you cease sending me

Speaker 2: the 10 pills you've been sending me.

Speaker 1: They sent it again this month,

Speaker 2: and I'm guessing you're charging this to my Medicare.

Speaker 1: Let me help you out, Craig.

Speaker 2: Can I just have you confirm your date of birth?

Speaker 1: 9-14-55.

Speaker 2: Thank you so much.

Speaker 1: Your VIP status, oh, I see the doctor has you

Speaker 2: on monthly refills, which you do not have to have.

Speaker 1: How's the medication working out for you?

Speaker 2: It doesn't work.

Speaker 1: It's no better than the original.

Speaker 2: Yeah, that's what I was asking,

Speaker 1: because it looks here, the pharmacy made an error

Speaker 2: and just sent you just regular, generic Viagras.

Speaker 1: Give me one second.

Speaker 2: I'm gonna get you out of replacement,

Speaker 1: and then I'm gonna tell you how you can confirm

Speaker 2: you received the correct medication.

Speaker 1: Okay, perfect, okay, so when you get this new bottle,

Speaker 2: they're gonna be shipping out to you today.

Speaker 1: So when you get this new bottle in the mail,

Speaker 2: on the bottle, it's gonna say AGV,

Speaker 1: but it's also going to say Greenstone,

Speaker 2: and Greenstone is the name of Pfizer's manufacturer

Speaker 1: in France, and then on the pills,

Speaker 2: the only number imprinted is going to be

Speaker 1: the number 100 for the milligrams,

Speaker 2: and those are the two ways you can confirm

Speaker 1: you received the Pfizer AGV,

Speaker 2: because right now, I know your bottle says APCO,

Speaker 1: and then on your pills, the letters AC is imprinted,

Speaker 2: followed by the numbers 390 or 340 or something.

Speaker 1: So just go ahead and toss those in the trash can,

Speaker 2: and then I'm gonna pause your refills for six months.

Speaker 1: I'm gonna pause it till July 31st of 2026,

Speaker 2: and then I'll give you my extension,

Speaker 1: so you can call me back and let me know

Speaker 2: how the AGV works out for you.

Speaker 1: That's all right, just cancel the thing.

Speaker 2: Don't bother sending me anything else.

Speaker 1: I'm good.

Speaker 2: Okay, no problem, Craig, all right.

Speaker 1: You're canceled, have a good one.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: Bye.
